GAFFNEY v. PRUETT. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. October 13, 1902.) No. 1,133. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Eastern District of Texas. J. F. Lanier (George C. Greer and H. B. Short, on the brief), for plaintiff in error. Presly K. Ewing and S. R. Perry-man (Perryman & Kottwitz and Ewing & Ring, on the brief), for defendant in error.

Before PARDEE, McCORMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the circuit court is affirmed
